      "writtenOn": "2019-01-09T02:43:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We can rename VMs to Config now, but it wouldn\u0027t have solved this problem (it would\u0027ve gone from \"process\" triggers \"processVMs\" to \"process\" triggers \"processConfig\"). The reason I didn\u0027t use Config initially is because it kind of looks odd having two configs: Kinds and Config, I thought Kinds and VMs made more sense, but I guess it doesn\u0027t really matter since Kinds is temporary. Plus calling it VMs introduced other stupidities (hard to distinguish between a plurality of VM entities and one VMs entity).\n\nI\u0027ll use scheduleX triggers X and rename VMs to Config then.",
      "parentUuid": "c4e30c58_0513f662",
